Western Cape police spokesman Captain FC van Wyk said the girl was walking along Robert Sobukwe Road last week when a man kidnapped her. She was "taken to a shack where she was repeatedly raped by him and his friends. They kept her at the residence and released her the next day."The men are between 18 and 20 years old.The case was postponed to Friday for a bail hearing.Eric Ntabazalila, National Prosecuting Authority spokesman in the Western Cape, said more men were involved. "There were 10 men who raped the girl and she has positively identified the seven who have been arrested."Last week, the High Court in Cape Town sentenced Mthunzi Hlomane, the " UCT rapist", to nine life terms for rape.